.TH gui_dump_picture  22.14 "Fri Oct 06 02:12:27 2023" 
.SH Name \fBgui_dump_picture\fR \-  Saves a snapshot of the layout or specified window with the specified name in the current directory. You can specify the size as well as the format in which you want to save the snapshot. The command also prints out overlay maps with legends
.SH Syntax \fBgui_dump_picture\fR  [-help]  <filename>   [-format {BMP GIF JPG JPEG PNG PBM PGM PPM XBM XPM}]  [-width <integer_value> -height <integer_value>]  [-window <string>]
.P Saves a snapshot of the layout or specified window with the specified name in the current directory. You can specify the size as well as the format in which you want to save the snapshot. The command also prints out overlay maps with legends.
.P You can use this command at any stage of the design flow.  
.SH Parameters   "\fB-help\fR" Prints a brief description that includes type and default information for each gui_dump_picture parameter.  For a detailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use the man command:  man gui_dump_picture  "\fB<filename>\fR" Specifies the name of the picture file as a string. You can specify the file extension as well.  Note: The file extension you specify does not control the format of the picture. The picture file is dumped in the PNG format by default or the format you explicitly specify with -format. For example, the following command saves the testShot picture file in the PNG format:  innovus 34> gui_dump_picture testShot.gif  <current_directory>@file testShot.gif  testShot.gif: PNG image data, 540 x 688, 8-bit/color RGB, non-interlaced  "\fB-format {BMP GIF JPG JPEG PNG PBM PGM PPM XBM XPM}\fR" Specifies the format of the picture file.  Default: PNG  "\fB-height <integer_value>\fR" Specifies the height of the picture as an integral value.  Note: The -width parameter is required when -height is specified.  Min: 100  Max: 20000  "\fB-width <integer_value>\fR" Specifies the width of the picture as an integral value.  Note: The -height parameter is required when -width is specified.  Min: 100  Max: 20000  "\fB-window <string>\fR" Specifies the ID of the window that you want to dump. You can use the following IDs:
.RS  "*" 2 For Layout Viewer: designview.win  "*" 2 For Cell Viewer:
.uiCellView.win
.RE   If -window is not specified, the layout window is dumped out by default. 
.SH Examples
.RS  "*" 2 The following command captures the layout window and saves it in the default PNG format with the name <test2> and the dimensions 1000 x 1000 in the current directory:  gui_dump_picture test2 -width 1000 height 1000
.RE
.RS  "*" 2 The following command captures the layout window and saves it in the GIF format with the name <test1.gif> in the current directory:  gui_dump_picture -format GIF test1.gif  "*" 2 The following command captures the layout viewer window and saves it in PNG format with the name testShot.png in the current directory:  gui_dump_picture testShot.png -window designview.win  Note: You must have the layout viewer open.  (<Image> To view the image, refer to the Innovus Text Command Reference - Release 22.1 manual.)  "*" 2 The following command captures the view in the cell viewer window and saves it in PNG format with the name testCell.png in the current directory:  gui_dump_picture testCell.png -window
.uiCellView.win  (<Image> To view the image, refer to the Innovus Text Command Reference - Release 22.1 manual.) 
.RE 
.SH Related Information
.RS  "*" 2 createSnapshot  "*" 2 dumpPictures  "*" 2 dumpToGIF
.RE
.P
